message.entry: Dimension must be 1 or 2 for a 2-D table.
When generating code, dimension argument must be constant.
All event tables must either have the ''{0}'' property set to the same variable name or the property must be unset across all event tables.
All event tables that have the ''{0}'' property set, must have it set to the same variable name.

This operation is not supported when one event table has the 'EventLengthsVariable' property set and another event table has the 'EventEndsVariable' property set. Convert all event tables to either use event lengths or event end times.
In code generation, while concatenating tables, the first variable-size table cannot be 0x0 at runtime.
